 The convict had admitted that he had, in 2019, been convicted for a similar offence by a magistrates’ court and sentenced to community service. The magistrate, after listening to the facts presented by the police prosecutor, sentenced Isola to one-year imprisonment, without an option of fine. Vanguard News Nigeria Shina Abubakar - Osogbo A Magistrate court sitting in Osogbo, Osun State has convicted and sentenced one Saheed Isola, 40, to one-year imprisonment for stealing block mould. Isola was arraigned on Wednesday on a count bordering on stealing. Fagboyinbo alleged that the convict unlawfully entered into the shop of one… October 14, 2020 In "Metro" By Shina Abubakar An Osun Magistrate court sitting in Osogbo the state capital on Monday sentenced a 20-year-old Mechanics Ibrahim Kolapo to prison for stealing aluminium flat sheets. ASP Abiodun Fagboyinbo had alleged that the defendant unlawfully jumped through a fence and entered into the dwelling house of one Sola… August 24, 2020 In "News" An Abeokuta Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday jailed 27-year-old Lekan Famuyiwa seven years for stealing a welding machine valued at N70,000. January 9, 2019 In "Crime Alert"